modules.description: This module enables declarative construction and manipulation of DOM elements using reactive programming with the `Lwd.t` type, offering typed constructors for both standard elements (e.g., `div`, `span`, `input`) and void elements (e.g., `img`, `hr`). It operates on `cons` and `void_cons` types to enforce HTML semantic rules, supporting dynamic attributes, event handlers, and nested content. Use cases include building interactive web interfaces with type-safe, composable UI components that automatically update in response to state changes.

This module provides a declarative framework for building reactive web interfaces using the `Lwd.t` type, enabling type-safe construction of DOM elements with dynamic attributes, event handlers, and nested content. It distinguishes between `cons` for standard elements allowing children and `void_cons` for self-closing elements, ensuring semantic HTML correctness. Developers can create interactive UI components like input forms or dynamic lists that automatically update in response to state changes. Example usage includes binding an input field's value to a reactive variable and updating a displayed counter in real time.
